node.text:
It’s still surreal to think that girls and boys across the country are playing with a Tessa Virtue Barbie® Doll, imagining themselves in my shoes (or skates)! As the cooler weather sets in, I can’t help but think about being out on the rink. #Throwback to early March when I had a blast skating with this group of future superstars. I hope, through imaginative play with the doll, that all kids across Canada will be encouraged to set goals and work hard to reach their limitless potential.
@barbie #barbie #YouCanBeAnything #ad

node.text:
After selling out in less than 24 hours, my @maccosmeticscanada lipstick is now back in stock in Canada! I filmed this little video showcasing my everyday makeup routine ... I’m certainly no expert, but it’s fun to share some of my go-to tips and techniques! Maybe self-isolation at home will provide a good opportunity to explore some other looks 🤷🏻‍♀️🧖🏻‍♀️
Check out the link in my bio to try my new shade 💋

node.text:
One of the highlights of summer 2021 was celebrating my mom’s birthday. It was magical in every way, just like she is ✨

I’d love to thank the local London businesses that made it all happen! 

💐@taniafloral was the ultimate party planner and of course, created the most beautiful flower arrangements

🌱@susanjoryinteriors provided the PERFECT setting and ambiance with her enchanting backyard venue

🍝 @blackfriarsbistro served delicious plates with elegance and style

🎂 @helmbaked made an angel food cake that tasted heavenly

🎶 #blackbeltjones played music that set the tone for the happiest, most relaxing vibe for quality family time

And special thanks to moment capturer extraordinaire, @richellehunter, for giving us photos to cherish and @tobinviscomms for a home run video montage 📸❤️
